@startuml Profiles Subsystem Sequence Diagram

title CIMUtil - Profile Transformation Sequence

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

participant "ProfileBuildlets\n[CIMToolPlugin]" as ORCH #LightSteelBlue
participant "ProfileModel" as PM #LightBlue
participant "Refactory" as REF #LightGreen
participant "ProfileClass" as PC #LightGreen
participant "ProfileSerializer" as SER #LightCoral
participant "Saxon Transformer\n[XSLT Engine]" as SAX #LightYellow

== Profile Loading ==

activate ORCH
ORCH -> ORCH : loadOntModel(profileFile)
note right of ORCH
    Reads the .owl profile file
    into a Kena OntModel using
    IO.read() (Turtle format)
end note
ORCH -> ORCH : loadOntModel(schemaFile(s))
note right of ORCH
    Reads the background schema
    OntModel (merged if multiple).
    In the CLI path (CLIProfileTransformer)
    this is the pre-parsed schema from
    CLISchemaParser.
end note

== Profile Model Construction ==

ORCH -> PM : new ProfileModel()
activate PM
ORCH -> PM : setOntModel(profileModel)
note right of PM
    Stores the profile OWL model.
    Constructs a Refactory over it
    which becomes the bridge between
    the OWL graph and the ProfileClass
    domain object layer.
end note
ORCH -> PM : setBackgroundModel(backgroundModel)
PM -> REF : new Refactory(profileModel, backgroundModel)
activate REF
note right of REF
    Refactory is the central profile
    editing facade. It holds references
    to both the profile OntModel and the
    full background schema OntModel, and
    provides operations to add/remove
    classes and properties in the profile.
end note
PM --> ORCH : messageModel
deactivate REF

== ProfileSerializer Setup ==

ORCH -> SER : new ProfileSerializer(messageModel)
activate SER
note right of SER
    ProfileSerializer extends AbstractReader
    (a SAX XMLReader). It wraps the
    ProfileModel tree and emits SAX events
    when Saxon calls parse() during the
    XSLT transformation.
end note
ORCH -> SER : setBaseURI(namespace)
ORCH -> SER : setOntologyURI(ontologyURI)
ORCH -> SER : setCopyrightMultiLine(text)
ORCH -> SER : setCopyrightSingleLine(text)
ORCH -> SER : setBuilderParameters(params)
ORCH -> SER : setNamespacePrefixesBuilderParameter(map)

ORCH -> SER : setStyleSheet(xsltStream, XSDGEN)
note right of SER
    Compiles the XSLT stylesheet into
    a cached Templates object via Saxon's
    TransformerFactory. For TEXT builders
    an additional "indent" post-processor
    stylesheet is chained via addStyleSheet().
end note

== XSLT Transformation ==

ORCH -> SER : write(outputStream)
activate SER

SER -> SER : build SAXSource(this, InputSource)
note right of SER
    ProfileSerializer IS the SAX source.
    Saxon will call parse() on it to pull
    XML events rather than reading from
    a file or string.
end note

SER -> SAX : transformer.transform(saxSource, streamResult)
activate SAX

note right of SAX
    Saxon drives the transformation by
    calling ProfileSerializer.parse() which
    triggers emit() to walk the ProfileModel
    tree and fire SAX events:
    - startDocument / endDocument
    - startElement / endElement
    - characters (for string values)
    The XSLT stylesheet processes these
    events and writes the output format
    (XSD, JSON Schema, HTML, RDFS, etc.)
    to the StreamResult (output file).
end note

SAX -> SER : parse() [SAX pull]
activate SER
SER -> SER : emit(model.getRoot())
note right of SER
    Walks the ProfileModel node tree:
    CatalogNode → EnvelopeNode →
      MessageNode → ElementNode →
        SubTypeNode / SuperTypeNode /
        EnumValueNode
    Each node type emits its corresponding
    XML element structure as SAX events.
end note

SER -> PM : getRoot() / iterate nodes
activate PM

loop for each node in ProfileModel tree
    PM -> PC : getProfileClasses(profileModel)
    activate PC
    note right of PC
        ProfileClass wraps an OntResource
        and exposes the profile-level view:
        - getBaseClass() — the CIM class being profiled
        - getProperties() — restricted properties
        - getPropertyInfo() — cardinality, type info
        - getSuperClasses() / getSubClasses()
        - isRestrictedEnum() / isUnion()
        These are read by ProfileSerializer
        to generate the SAX event stream.
    end note
    PC --> PM : properties, cardinalities, supertypes
    deactivate PC
    PM --> SER : SAX events for node
    deactivate PM
end

SER --> SAX : SAX event stream complete
deactivate SER

SAX --> SER : transformed output written\nto OutputStream
deactivate SAX
SER --> ORCH : output file written
deactivate SER
deactivate SER

== SchemaGenerator Path (direct OWL/RDFS output) ==

note over ORCH, PC
    A separate path exists for RDFS and OWL schema output builders that do not use
    the SAX + XSLT pipeline above. SchemaGenerator subclasses (OWLGenerator,
    RDFSGenerator, RDFSBasedGenerator) traverse ProfileClass objects directly and
    emit OWL/RDFS triples into a result OntModel:

        SchemaGenerator.run()
            scanProfiles()    — iterates ProfileClass.getProfileClasses()
            scanProperties()  — reads ProfileClass.getProperties() / PropertyInfo
            generateClass()   — emits OWL class triples
            generateProperty() — emits OWL property triples
            generateLattice() — emits rdfs:subClassOf triples

    The resulting OntModel is then serialized to RDF/XML directly, bypassing
    ProfileSerializer entirely. Reorganizer subclasses (ProfileReorganizer,
    SchemaReorganizer) apply a structural normalization pass over the profile
    OntModel before either pipeline runs, ensuring cardinalities and class
    hierarchies conform to IEC 61970-501 rules.
end note

deactivate PM
deactivate ORCH

@enduml
